TO UN announces new objectives with the case of the poverty abatement
The United Nations begin immediately now on with the preparation of a series of new objectives with which the twelve years ago announced millennium development objectives for the poverty abatement are supposed to be replaced.
In the front end of the UN-peak for lasting development which began at the evening in Rio de Janeiro Australian diplomats played a decisive role with the case of the advance for „lasting development objectives" which are supposed to replace the 2015 millennium objectives running out.
You were picked up into the definitive draft of the document that will be adopted by world-political leaders, including Ms Gillard, with the case of the peak.
UN-secretary-general Ban Ki-moon declared at the evening on the peak the time came „to think about the national interests out".
„I am pleased with the member states agreeing upon tackling a process with which universal, lasting development objectives are supposed to be agreed", he said.
„These objectives will base themselves on our progress from the millennium development objectives and form an integral component of the framework for the development after 2015.
I will not shun from any efforts to transform this mandate given to me by the member states in order to realize our vision of the lasting development objectives that base on the success of the millennium objectives
